{# ============================================================================
   ARG-058 / B6-T01 ‚Äî XMP metadata template consumed by the ``pdfx`` package.

   Rendered by ``LatexBackend.render`` to ``<tmpdir>/report.xmpdata`` whenever
   ``pdfa_mode=True``. pdfx auto-discovers the file by basename (must equal
   ``\jobname.xmpdata``) and serialises the keys below into the PDF/A-2u
   XMP metadata stream embedded in the document catalog.

   Keep keys in sync with ``hypersetup{pdftitle=...}`` in each tier template:
   pdfx writes the XMP, hyperref writes the legacy /Info dictionary; the two
   MUST match for verapdf to accept the file as PDF/A-2u compliant.

   Context inputs (defaults provided so the template never crashes when
   the caller forgets a key):
     * ``tier``         ‚Äî "asgard" | "midgard" | "valhalla".
     * ``tier_label``   ‚Äî human-readable tier name for the title.
     * ``tenant_id``    ‚Äî opaque tenant identifier (for keywords only).
     * ``scan_id``      ‚Äî opaque scan identifier (for keywords only).
     * ``creator``      ‚Äî fixed by the renderer to the cycle ID for stability.
     * ``language``     ‚Äî defaults to "en-US"; override via Jinja context.
   ============================================================================ #}
\Title{ARGUS Security Posture Report --- {{ tier_label | default('Tier') }}}
\Author{ARGUS}
\Subject{Security assessment report (tier={{ tier | default('midgard') }})}
\Keywords{security, pentest, vulnerability, ARGUS, tier:{{ tier | default('midgard') }}}
\Creator{ {{- creator | default('ARGUS Cycle 6') -}} }
\Producer{LaTeX with pdfx (PDF/A-2u)}
\Language{ {{- language | default('en-US') -}} }
\Org{ARGUS}
\Copyrighted{True}
\CopyrightText{Confidential. ARGUS internal report.}
